	 <title>System.Sum</title> 
	 <para></para> 
	 <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Remarks</bridgehead> 
	 <para>This operator is an aggregate operator that returns the arithmetic
		  sum of all of the values in the specified expression. In the case where there
		  are no rows then the operator will return 0.</para> 
	 <example> 
		  <title>Example</title> 
		  <programlisting>select Employee group add { Sum(ID) IDSum };</programlisting> 
		  <programlisting>IDSum
-----
21</programlisting> 
	 </example> 
